## Summary: Task Table Schema and Task Management in minnetonka-v1

Based on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's a complete analysis of the task table schema and how tasks are created/updated:

### 1. Task Table Schema (Lines 92-119 in `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/minnetonka-v1/schema/surreal-schema.surql`)

```sql
DEFINE TABLE task SCHEMAFULL;
DEFINE FIELD title ON task TYPE string;
DEFINE FIELD description ON task TYPE option<string>;
DEFINE FIELD description_entries ON task TYPE option<array<object>>;
DEFINE FIELD description_entries[*].text ON task TYPE string;
DEFINE FIELD description_entries[*].source ON task TYPE option<record>;
DEFINE FIELD description_entries[*].created_at ON task TYPE datetime;
DEFINE FIELD owner ON task TYPE option<record<person>>;
DEFINE FIELD owner_name ON task TYPE option<string>;
DEFINE FIELD deadline ON task TYPE option<datetime>;
DEFINE FIELD status ON task TYPE string;  // NO CONSTRAINT - accepts any string
DEFINE FIELD priority ON task TYPE option<string>
  ASSERT $value IN ["low", "medium", "high", "critical"] OR $value IS NONE;
DEFINE FIELD created_at ON task TYPE datetime;
DEFINE FIELD updated_at ON task TYPE option<datetime>;
DEFINE FIELD source_message ON task TYPE option<record<message>>;
DEFINE FIELD source_commit ON task TYPE option<record<git_commit>>;
DEFINE FIELD extraction_confidence ON task TYPE option<float> ASSERT $value = NONE OR ($value >= 0 AND $value <= 1);
DEFINE FIELD extracted_at ON task TYPE option<datetime>;
DEFINE FIELD embedding ON task TYPE option<array<float>>;
DEFINE FIELD category ON task TYPE option<string>
  ASSERT $value IN ["engineering", "research", "marketing", "operations", "design", "sales"] OR $value IS NONE;
DEFINE FIELD workspace ON task TYPE record<workspace>;
DEFINE INDEX task_status_deadline ON task FIELDS status, deadline;
DEFINE INDEX task_source_message ON task FIELDS source_message;
DEFINE INDEX task_source_commit ON task FIELDS source_commit;
DEFINE INDEX task_workspace ON task FIELDS workspace;
DEFINE INDEX idx_task_embedding ON task FIELDS embedding HNSW DIMENSION 1536 DIST COSINE;
```

**Key observation:** `status` field has **NO CONSTRAINT** - it accepts any string value. This is important as it's used throughout the code with various values.

### 2. Task Status Values Used in the Codebase

From searching `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/minnetonka-v1/app/src/server/mcp/mcp-queries.ts` (line 424-436) and other files:

**Active task statuses:**
- `"todo"` - New tasks created via `createSubtask()` (line 326)
- `"in_progress"` - Auto-set when agent session starts (line 503 in mcp-queries.ts)
- `"blocked"` - Checked when computing parent task status rollup (line 425)
- `"ready"` - Checked as transition state (line 501)

**Completed task statuses:**
- `"done"` - Final completion state (line 424)
- `"completed"` - Alternative final completion state (line 424)

**MCP-level queries** (`/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/minnetonka-v1/app/src/server/mcp/mcp-route.ts`, line 859):
```
SELECT title, status FROM task WHERE workspace = $ws AND status IN ["todo", "in_progress"]
```

### 3. Places Where Tasks Are Created

#### A. Work Item Accept Route (`/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/minnetonka-v1/app/src/server/entities/work-item-accept-route.ts`, lines 72-83)
```typescript
if (item.kind === "task") {
  const taskRecord = new RecordId("task", entityId);
  await deps.surreal.create(taskRecord).content({
    title: item.title,
    status: "open",  // Uses "open" status (NOT in other task creation paths!)
    workspace: workspaceRecord,
    ...(item.category ? { category: item.category } : {}),
    ...(item.priority ? { priority: item.priority } : {}),
    ...(embedding ? { embedding } : {}),
    created_at: now,
    updated_at: now,
  });
}
```

#### B. Create Work Item Tool (`/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/minnetonka-v1/app/src/server/chat/tools/create-work-item.ts`, lines 83-94)
```typescript
if (input.kind === "task") {
  const taskRecord = new RecordId("task", entityId);
  await deps.surreal.create(taskRecord).content({
    title: input.title,
    status: "open",  // Same as accept route
    workspace: context.workspaceRecord,
    ...(input.category ? { category: input.category } : {}),
    ...(input.priority ? { priority: input.priority } : {}),
    ...(embedding ? { embedding } : {}),
    created_at: now,
    updated_at: now,
  });
}
```

#### C. Create Subtask (`/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/minnetonka-v1/app/src/server/mcp/mcp-queries.ts`, lines 324-332)
```typescript
await input.surreal.create(taskRecord).content({
  title: input.title,
  status: "todo",  // Uses "todo" status for subtasks
  created_at: now,
  updated_at: now,
  workspace: input.workspaceRecord,
  ...(input.category ? { category: input.category } : parentTask.category ? { category: parentTask.category } : {}),
  ...(input.rationale ? { description: input.rationale } : {}),
});
```

**Status inconsistency note:** Tasks created from work items use `"open"`, but subtasks use `"todo"`. This is a discrepancy in the codebase.

### 4. Task Status Updates

#### Task Status Update Endpoint (`/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/minnetonka-v1/app/src/server/mcp/mcp-route.ts`, lines 545-564)
```typescript
async function handleUpdateTaskStatus(workspaceId: string, request: Request): Promise<Response> {
  const body = await parseJsonBody<{ task_id: string; status: string; notes?: string }>(request);
  if (!body.status) return jsonError("status is required", 400);

  const taskRecord = new RecordId("task", body.task_id);
  const result = await updateTaskStatus({
    surreal,
    taskRecord,
    status: body.status,
    notes: body.notes,
  });
}
```

#### Update Task Status Function (`/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/minnetonka-v1/app/src/server/mcp/mcp-queries.ts`, lines 365-376)
```typescript
export async function updateTaskStatus(input: {
  surreal: Surreal;
  taskRecord: RecordId<"task", string>;
  status: string;
  notes?: string;
}): Promise<{ task_id: string; status: string; parent_status?: string }> {
  const now = new Date();

  await input.surreal.update(input.taskRecord).merge({
    status: input.status,
    updated_at: now,
  });
  // ... handles notes appending and parent task rollup
}
```

### 5. Session-Related Fields on Tables

New agent session fields were added in migration `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/minnetonka-v1/schema/migrations/20260304_agent_session_and_subtask.surql`:

**New `agent_session` table** (lines 8-30):
```sql
DEFINE TABLE OVERWRITE agent_session SCHEMAFULL;
DEFINE FIELD agent ON agent_session TYPE string;
DEFINE FIELD directory ON agent_session TYPE string;
DEFINE FIELD started_at ON agent_session TYPE datetime;
DEFINE FIELD ended_at ON agent_session TYPE option<datetime>;
DEFINE FIELD workspace ON agent_session TYPE record<workspace>;
DEFINE FIELD project ON agent_session TYPE record<project>;
DEFINE FIELD task_id ON agent_session TYPE option<record<task>>;
DEFINE FIELD summary ON agent_session TYPE option<string>;
DEFINE FIELD decisions_made ON agent_session TYPE option<array<record<decision>>>;
DEFINE FIELD questions_asked ON agent_session TYPE option<array<record<question>>>;
DEFINE FIELD tasks_progressed ON agent_session TYPE option<array<object>>;
DEFINE FIELD tasks_progressed[*].task_id ON agent_session TYPE record<task>;
DEFINE FIELD tasks_progressed[*].from_status ON agent_session TYPE string;
DEFINE FIELD tasks_progressed[*].to_status ON agent_session TYPE string;
DEFINE FIELD files_changed ON agent_session TYPE option<array<object>>;
DEFINE FIELD files_changed[*].path ON agent_session TYPE string;
DEFINE FIELD files_changed[*].change_type ON agent_session TYPE string
  ASSERT $value IN ["created", "modified", "deleted"];
DEFINE FIELD created_at ON agent_session TYPE datetime;
```

**On `task` table:** No direct session-linking field (but sessions reference tasks via `task_id` field).

**On `observation` table** (migration `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/minnetonka-v1/schema/migrations/20260304_observation_coding_agent_fields.surql`):
```sql
DEFINE FIELD observation_type ON observation TYPE option<string>
  ASSERT $value IN ["contradiction", "duplication", "missing", "deprecated", "pattern", "anomaly"] OR $value IS NONE;
DEFINE FIELD source_session ON observation TYPE option<record<agent_session>>;
```

### 6. Related Tables/Relations

**Task hierarchy:**
- `subtask_of TYPE RELATION IN task OUT task` (line 33 in migration) - task-to-task parent relationships

**Task scope:**
- `belongs_to TYPE RELATION IN task OUT feature | project` (line 326 in schema)
- `has_task TYPE RELATION IN feature OUT task` (line 276 in schema)
- `depends_on TYPE RELATION IN task | feature OUT task | feature` (line 286 in schema)

**Session relations** (new):
- `produced TYPE RELATION IN agent_session OUT decision` (line 37 in migration)
- `asked TYPE RELATION IN agent_session OUT question` (line 40 in migration)
- `progressed TYPE RELATION IN agent_session OUT task` (line 43 in migration) - tracks status transitions

---

### Key Findings

1. **Task status is unconstrained** - accepts any string value, though only specific values are actually used
2. **Status inconsistency** - work item tasks use `"open"`, subtasks use `"todo"`
3. **Status transitions tracked** - agent sessions record `from_status` → `to_status` transitions
4. **Auto-promotion** - when an agent session starts with task scope, status auto-transitions to `"in_progress"` if currently `"todo"` or `"ready"`
5. **Subtask rollup** - parent task status is computed from child statuses (completed if all done/completed, blocked if any blocked, etc.)

